"title":"Palliative Care",
"jsonContent":{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s10",
"title":{
"__html":"Palliative Care"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b7230d",
"children":[
"Palliative Care"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s10_0",
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"82d23f",
"children":[
"Palliative care may be provided concurrently with life-prolonging therapies or with therapies with curative intent. Hospice, on the other hand, is a specialized type of palliative care that is reserved for patients in the terminal phase of their disease, arbitrarily defined as the last 6 months of life."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s10_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Acute and Chronic Pain at the End of Life"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"089a9c",
"children":[
"Acute and Chronic Pain at the End of Life"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b1bf15",
"children":[
"Pharmacologic management of pain progresses in a stepwise fashion."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9db287",
"children":[
"Use acetaminophen, aspirin, or ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
" for mild to moderate pain."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1347a8",
"children":[
"If pain persists or increases, add a low-dose or low-potency opioid (e.g., oxycodone). Avoid codeine and tramadol."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7c4618",
"children":[
"Increase opioid potency (e.g., morphine) or add higher doses for persistent or moderate to severe pain at onset."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a42f5c",
"children":[
"Add adjuvant agents (tricyclic antidepressants, gabapentinoids, or carbamazepine) at any step."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"94cc96",
"children":[
"Prescribe around-the-clock analgesics for persistent, chronic pain rather than as needed."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s10_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0bce25",
"children":[
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Opioids do not have an analgesic efficacy ceiling"
]
},
" and can be titrated upward as needed until limiting adverse effects appear. Combination opioid-acetaminophen limits the dose range because of potential acetaminophen toxicity. Common adverse effects of opioids include constipation, sedation, nausea, and itching (not from an allergy). In patients using short-acting opioids who require longer lasting relief, long-acting agents are appropriate; however, long-acting opioids should not be the initial opioid prescribed in opioid-na√Øve patients."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"43a33f",
"children":[
"Warnings about opioid use:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"eaed71",
"children":[
"Fentanyl should be used only in opioid-tolerant patients."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3c4bc3",
"children":[
"Meperidine is not recommended for pain because of an increased risk for seizure."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"650199",
"children":[
"Tramadol has significant drug interactions, especially with other serotonergic medications."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"13e76f",
"children":[
"Methadone should be initiated and titrated only by experts."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"31ccac",
"children":[
"In the administration of opioids, oral routes are preferred (do not use ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"intramuscular",
"children":[
"IM"
]
},
")."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bc64aa",
"children":[
"Sublingual or subcutaneous routes may be used for patients unable to use an oral route."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6f10cd",
"children":[
"Neuropathic pain is characterized by burning, tingling, or lancinating pain. Add tricyclic antidepressants, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"serotonin-norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor",
"children":[
"SNRI"
]
},
"s"
]
},
" (venlafaxine, duloxetine), or antiepileptic medications (gabapentin, pregabalin, carbamazepine) to the pain regimen."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"30107f",
"children":[
"Treat bone pain with anti-inflammatory medications (NSAIDs or glucocorticoids) or bisphosphonates (pamidronate, zoledronate)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"df59a9",
"children":[
"All patients receiving scheduled opioids should be taking a scheduled bowel regimen to prevent constipation, in this order:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"06abd9",
"children":[
"stimulant laxative with or without docusate"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"012934",
"children":[
"osmotic agent (",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"polyethylene glycol",
"children":[
"PEG"
]
},
","
]
},
" sorbitol, or lactulose)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5bf014",
"children":[
"naldemedine, naloxegol, or methylnaltrexone"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gm_s10_inline_t2"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s10_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Dyspnea"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"e70b0a",
"children":[
"Dyspnea"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4ba2c1",
"children":[
"Treat reversible causes of dyspnea, such as pleural effusions, infection, and anemia. Systemic opioids are the standard of care for refractory dyspnea in advanced disease. Patients who experience dyspnea-related anxiety and continue to experience dyspnea despite opioids may benefit from short-acting benzodiazepines."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"86cdf1",
"children":[
"Oxygen supplementation is helpful if the patient is hypoxic but is otherwise ineffective."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b1e8fa",
"children":[
"Fans are effective in reducing dyspnea in nonhypoxic patients."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s10_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Depression and Anxiety"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"e3d63d",
"children":[
"Depression and Anxiety"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"821f67",
"children":[
"It is difficult to distinguish grief from depression. Helplessness, hopelessness, worthlessness, guilt, and anhedonia are signs of depression rather than normal grief."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"aaad9e",
"children":[
"Depression will respond to typical pharmacologic and nonpharmacologic therapy. If prognosis is less than 6 weeks, use a psychostimulant with a faster onset, such as methylphenidate. Benzodiazepines can help reduce anxiety in a palliative care setting."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s10_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Anorexia"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b11759",
"children":[
"Anorexia"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"36056d",
"children":[
"Artificial nutrition in cachexia of advanced disease does not improve morbidity or mortality, nor does it reduce aspiration pneumonia risk. Medications used to stimulate appetite (progesterones, dronabinol, glucocorticoids) do not improve morbidity or mortality."
]
}
]
}
]
},
